    ],
    "notes": "Detection should focus on arp.exe spawned by processes residing outside trusted system paths (e.g., parent.executable matching AppData, Temp, or ProgramData paths). The critical differentiator is process.parent.executable — legitimate arp.exe invocations originate from cmd.exe, powershell.exe, or known Windows diagnostics binaries in System32, NOT from user-space AppData binaries. A high-fidelity rule would combine: process.name == 'arp.exe' AND process.parent.executable matching *\\AppData\\* OR *\\Temp\\* OR *\\ProgramData\\*. Rapid successive arp.exe calls (sequence events 1+2) and output redirection to AppData (event 3) are strong behavioral indicators of automated host discovery by a C2 implant."
  },
